Health Minister, Zweli Mkhize visited healthcare facilities in Gauteng. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Health minister Zweli Mkhize conducted an oversight inspection at hospitals in Pretoria on Tuesday. The Health Department confirmed 9,010 new COVID-19 cases in South Africa on Monday, taking the cumulative number of cases to 1,346,936. The department has also confirmed a further 344 deaths. This takes the death toll to 37,449.